org.jscripter.emu.gc
Class GC

java.lang.Object
  js.Disposable
      org.jscripter.emu.gc.GC
Direct Known Subclasses:
DFS, GCDOM
public abstract class GC
extends js.Disposable

An internal abstract base class for DOM-enabled visitors emulating garbage collection based finalization in JavaScript.

This class is only used internally by JS re-compiler implementations.

Author:
J.J.Liu (Jianjun Liu) at http://www.jscripter.org
JavaScript:
This class is only loaded and resolved by re-compiler implementations.

Field Detail

REFS

protected static final js.Index<java.lang.Integer> REFS

A global identifier for a configurable property of an object.

The identified configurable property of an object is a reference to an integer number that indicates how many counts the object are currently referenced by other live objects.

Since:
1.0
JavaScript:
Re-compilers must report error on end-users directly using this identifier.

setInterval

public static final js.ArrayLike<?> setInterval(js.core.JsFunction<?> f,
                                                java.lang.Number interval)

Internally executes code at periodic intervals, with finalization support simulating the JavaScript global function of the same name.

Note that the specified function is executed in the context of the Window object, that is, the Window object is the value of the this keyword of the executing context of the function. This is true even if the call to setTimeout(JsFunction, Number) occurred within a function with a longer scope chain.

Parameters:
f - A function to be periodically invoked.
interval - The interval, in milliseconds, between invocations of the function.
Returns:
A value that can be passed to clearInterval(ArrayLike) method to cancel the periodic execution of the function.
Since:
1.0
See Also:
clearInterval(ArrayLike), Js.setInterval(JsFunction), Js.setInterval(JsFunction, Number), Global.setInterval(JsFunction), Global.setInterval(JsFunction, Number), Global.setInterval(JsFunction), Global.setInterval(JsFunction, Number), Interval
JavaScript:
Re-compilers must report error on end-users directly using this method.

clearInterval

public static final void clearInterval(js.ArrayLike<?> intervalId)

Internally cancels periodic execution of code, with finalization support simulating the JavaScript global function of the same name.

This method stops the repeated execution of code that was started by a call to setInterval(JsFunction, Number). intervalId must be the value that was returned by a call to setInterval(JsFunction, Number).

Parameters:
intervalId - The value returned by the corresponding call to setInterval(JsFunction, Number).
Since:
1.0
See Also:
setInterval(JsFunction, Number), Js.setInterval(JsFunction, Number), Global.clearInterval(Object), Global.clearInterval(Object), Interval
JavaScript:
Re-compilers must report error on end-users directly using this method.

setTimeout

public static js.ArrayLike<?> setTimeout(js.core.JsFunction<?> f,
                                         java.lang.Number delay)

Internally executes code after a specified amount of time elapses, with finalization support simulating the JavaScript global function of the same name.

Note that this method executes the specified function only once. The function is executed in the context of the Window object, that is, the Window object is the value of the this keyword of the executing context of the function. This is true even if the call to setTimeout(JsFunction, Number) occurred within a function with a longer scope chain.

Parameters:
f - A function to be invoked after the delay has elapsed.
delay - The amount of time, in milliseconds, before the function should be executed.
Returns:
A value that can be passed to the clearTimeout(ArrayLike) method to cancel the execution of the function.
Since:
1.0
See Also:
clearTimeout(ArrayLike), Js.setTimeout(JsFunction), Js.setTimeout(JsFunction, Number), Global.setTimeout(JsFunction), Global.setTimeout(JsFunction, Number), Global.setTimeout(JsFunction), Global.setTimeout(JsFunction, Number), Timeout
JavaScript:
Re-compilers must report error on end-users directly using this method.

clearTimeout

public static final void clearTimeout(js.ArrayLike<?> timeoutId)

Internally cancels a pending timeout operation, with finalization support simulating the JavaScript global function of the same name.

This method cancels the execution of code that has been deferred with the setTimeout(JsFunction, Number) method. The timeoutId argument is a value returned by the call to setTimeout(JsFunction, Number) and identifies which deferred code to cancel.

Parameters:
timeoutId - A value returned by setTimeout(JsFunction, Number) that identifies the timeout to be canceled.
Since:
1.0
See Also:
setTimeout(JsFunction, Number), Js.setTimeout(JsFunction, Number), Js.clearTimeout(Object), Global.clearTimeout(Object), Global.clearTimeout(Object), Timeout
JavaScript:
Re-compilers must report error on end-users directly using this method.
